From peter da silva Subject Re DCC and MiniDisc next DAT DDS like story In article Tor Tor Olav Berntzen writes Another thing why a SCSI interface Because SCSI works well with removable media and works well with large capacity The floppy interface you suggest handles the former but it doesn't have any hooks for dealing with the you'd have to kludge Plus it's extremely low AND SCSI has gobs of room for expansion compared with a floppy I can just see it let's stick a a a tape drive and a MO drive all on the floppy The possibilities for unexpected collisions are enormous Peter da Silva ' Network Management Technologies Incorporated 'U West Airport Sugar Land TX USA Zure otsoa besarkatu al duzu gaur